    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="225"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d225">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2540/173–174.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Fox</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 418.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor, respectfully referring to my
                    No. 407 of the 11th instant, to inclose herewith clipping<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d225fn1">Not printed.</note> from the Financial <pb facs="0378"
                        n="276" xml:id="pg_276"/> Times of London, England, November 26, 1908, which
                    is an account of the meeting of the English bondholders of the Guayaquil &amp;
                    Quito Railway, at which the contract of September 30, 1908, between the
                    Government of Ecuador, the American stockholders, and the English bondholders of
                    the railway was duly ratified.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Williams C. Fox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
